Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.58,0:00:03.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, \Nthere are many people today\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.59,0:00:06.62,Default,,0,0,0,,who say that we’re not living \Nin the time of the end. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.62,0:00:10.23,Default,,0,0,0,,They say: “The world is just \Nthe same as it’s always been. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.23,0:00:13.56,Default,,0,0,0,,There are no real changes \Nthat have taken place.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.56,0:00:16.73,Default,,0,0,0,,But, of course, \Nwe know they’re deceiving themselves. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.73,0:00:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Never before have \Nso many people around the globe \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.80,0:00:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,openly practiced and flaunted \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.07,0:00:26.28,Default,,0,0,0,,sexual immorality, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.28,0:00:28.38,Default,,0,0,0,,not just among themselves \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.38,0:00:30.68,Default,,0,0,0,,but they’re seeing \Nthat it’s brought into the homes \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.68,0:00:35.25,Default,,0,0,0,,by means of Internet, \Ntelevision, and other means. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.25,0:00:38.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Never before has man had the power \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.29,0:00:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,to decimate entire populations \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.36,0:00:44.69,Default,,0,0,0,,by dropping just one bomb \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.69,0:00:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,or by means of chemical warfare. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.03,0:00:51.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Never before has there been \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.03,0:00:54.94,Default,,0,0,0,,such widespread lack of love \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.94,0:00:57.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and of natural affection \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.37,0:01:01.31,Default,,0,0,0,,that results in the death of children.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.31,0:01:04.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s interesting that some calculate \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.65,0:01:09.95,Default,,0,0,0,,that over one billion abortions \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.95,0:01:14.09,Default,,0,0,0,,have taken place since 1980. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.09,0:01:16.29,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s really something. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.29,0:01:19.56,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s just about the population of China\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.56,0:01:21.56,Default,,0,0,0,,—if you can imagine.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.56,0:01:24.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And that is something that’s accepted; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.50,0:01:27.30,Default,,0,0,0,,it’s commonplace in our day. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.30,0:01:30.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So some people think, \N‘Well, things haven’t changed.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.07,0:01:32.08,Default,,0,0,0,,But is that true? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.08,0:01:34.08,Default,,0,0,0,,No, quite to the contrary. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.08,0:01:36.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And something else \Nthat we’re fully aware of \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.21,0:01:38.98,Default,,0,0,0,,is that people around the earth \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.98,0:01:42.65,Default,,0,0,0,,are making a garbage dump \Nout of the planet that we live on\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.65,0:01:46.12,Default,,0,0,0,,—polluting the air, the seas, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.12,0:01:48.22,Default,,0,0,0,,the land. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.22,0:01:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And yet, some still insist \Nthat things haven’t changed. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.40,0:01:53.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, why is it? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.66,0:01:56.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do people have that attitude? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.60,0:01:59.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, part of it lies in \Nwhat the Scriptures tell us, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.34,0:02:02.84,Default,,0,0,0,,what Paul wrote \Nat 2 Corinthians 4:3, 4. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.84,0:02:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And there it says that Satan \N‘blinds the minds of the unbelievers.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.04,0:02:09.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And the “unbelievers” \Nare not just atheists. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.95,0:02:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The “unbelievers” are found \Nthroughout the churches of Christendom. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.78,0:02:15.79,Default,,0,0,0,,They don’t believe\N—really believe—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.79,0:02:18.69,Default,,0,0,0,,what the Bible has to say \Nabout prophecy, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.69,0:02:20.96,Default,,0,0,0,,about morality, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.96,0:02:23.93,Default,,0,0,0,,or that God is really going\Nto clean up this planet \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.93,0:02:26.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and that it’s going to be\Na wonderful new world\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.43,0:02:28.60,Default,,0,0,0,,of peace and happiness. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.60,0:02:30.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And so to help people \Nunderstand these things,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.70,0:02:32.27,Default,,0,0,0,,we go out and we preach. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.27,0:02:35.51,Default,,0,0,0,,We tell them \Nabout what Matthew 24 says\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.51,0:02:39.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and Mark 13 \Nand Luke 21 and 2 Timothy 3\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.41,0:02:41.54,Default,,0,0,0,,—that we’re living in the time of the end. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.54,0:02:43.55,Default,,0,0,0,,But there is something \Nwe have to remember \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.55,0:02:45.38,Default,,0,0,0,,if we get a little bit discouraged \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.38,0:02:48.28,Default,,0,0,0,,when people don’t respond \Nas we feel they should \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.28,0:02:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to all of the evidence \Nthat we see and we appreciate.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.79,0:02:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The Bible indicates very clearly \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.56,0:02:59.86,Default,,0,0,0,,that many people would not see the sign; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.86,0:03:03.63,Default,,0,0,0,,they would not accept \Nwhat the Bible has to say. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.63,0:03:05.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And what’s most interesting about that \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.87,0:03:08.14,Default,,0,0,0,,is that the people who ignore \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.14,0:03:11.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and who deny the sign \Nthat we’re living in the time of the end \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.94,0:03:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,are part of the sign themselves\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.38,0:03:17.15,Default,,0,0,0,,—what they do and the way they think. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.15,0:03:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Turn to Second Peter\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.99,0:03:27.86,Default,,0,0,0,,—2 Peter chapter 3. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.86,0:03:32.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And we’ll read verses 3 and 4\Nand the first line in verse 5\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.70,0:03:37.47,Default,,0,0,0,,—2 Peter 3:3, 4 \Nand the first line in verse 5. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.47,0:03:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Peter wrote: “First of all know this, \Nthat in the last days,” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.20,0:03:45.64,Default,,0,0,0,,so this is something Peter is saying \Nwould happen during our time, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.64,0:03:48.01,Default,,0,0,0,,“ridiculers will come with their ridicule, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.01,0:03:50.61,Default,,0,0,0,,“proceeding according to their own desires \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.61,0:03:53.85,Default,,0,0,0,,“and saying: \N‘Where is this promised presence of his? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.85,0:03:56.75,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Why, from the day \Nour forefathers fell asleep in death, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.75,0:03:59.62,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘all things are continuing exactly \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.62,0:04:02.49,Default,,0,0,0,,as they were from creation’s beginning.’” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.49,0:04:05.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And then the reason for it \Nis given in the next line: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.16,0:04:08.70,Default,,0,0,0,,“For they deliberately ignore this fact.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.70,0:04:11.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, here the fact was that they \Nignored the Flood of Noah’s day. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.77,0:04:15.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact for us today is that they \Nignore what the Bible clearly says \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.77,0:04:20.08,Default,,0,0,0,,or what Jesus said would be \Nthe sign of the last days. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.08,0:04:23.91,Default,,0,0,0,,So they don’t realize it, \Nbut they’re part of the fulfillment.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.91,0:04:27.45,Default,,0,0,0,,What contributes to an unbelieving attitude? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.45,0:04:31.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, one of the things \Nis what we could call gradualism. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.55,0:04:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The Watchtower \Nof January 15, 2014, paragraph 30, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.56,0:04:40.30,Default,,0,0,0,,or page 30, \Nparagraph 11 stated the following: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.30,0:04:43.40,Default,,0,0,0,,“It seems \Nthat the more familiar a situation is, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.40,0:04:46.34,Default,,0,0,0,,“the less people \Nare inclined to pay attention to it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.34,0:04:48.44,Default,,0,0,0,,“A steady decline in the morality \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.44,0:04:51.24,Default,,0,0,0,,“of society in general \Nmay seem less shocking \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.24,0:04:53.38,Default,,0,0,0,,“than a sudden, unexpected change \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.38,0:04:55.58,Default,,0,0,0,,in the behavior of a close acquaintance.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.58,0:04:57.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And then it says: \N“Nevertheless, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.58,0:05:01.28,Default,,0,0,0,,this gradual decay\Nof morality is dangerous.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.28,0:05:05.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And isn’t it true \Nthat most of us were raised \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.25,0:05:08.29,Default,,0,0,0,,in an environment \Nthat was not so good? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.29,0:05:13.13,Default,,0,0,0,,There were immoral things \Ntaking place around us, wars, crime. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.13,0:05:16.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And so people get to the point \Nwhere they accept it as normal. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.93,0:05:18.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And as it escalates, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.94,0:05:22.74,Default,,0,0,0,,it really doesn’t impress \Non them that ‘No!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.74,0:05:23.84,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Times have changed.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.84,0:05:27.47,Default,,0,0,0,,They’re becoming\Nfar worse than ever before.’\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.47,0:05:31.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Gradual decay of morality is dangerous.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.71,0:05:34.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It makes me think of an illustration \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.12,0:05:37.59,Default,,0,0,0,,about how to boil a frog. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.59,0:05:40.09,Default,,0,0,0,,If you heat up a pot \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.09,0:05:43.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and you have the water boiling \Nand drop a frog into it, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.73,0:05:45.63,Default,,0,0,0,,what’s going to happen? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.63,0:05:47.63,Default,,0,0,0,,He’s out of there; \Nhe’s not going to stay. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.63,0:05:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That frog isn’t stupid. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.00,0:05:52.67,Default,,0,0,0,,He hits the water, \Nand it’s terribly hot, and out he jumps. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.67,0:05:55.47,Default,,0,0,0,,But if you fill the pot with cool water, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.47,0:05:57.47,Default,,0,0,0,,drop the frog in, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.47,0:06:01.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and then \Ngradually (little by little) you heat it up \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.58,0:06:03.71,Default,,0,0,0,,until it gets to the boiling point, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.71,0:06:05.72,Default,,0,0,0,,he’s cooked! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.72,0:06:08.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And that’s what’s happening \Nin the world today. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.08,0:06:13.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The gradualism is not perceived \Nby people in the world, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.09,0:06:15.32,Default,,0,0,0,,but they’re being cooked. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.32,0:06:17.33,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s getting hot. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.33,0:06:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we know that wicked men \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.00,0:06:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,are going to continue to increase\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.00,0:06:25.13,Default,,0,0,0,,—impostors, \Nscoffing at the truth. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.13,0:06:29.81,Default,,0,0,0,,World conditions are escalating; \Nthey’re getting worse constantly. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.81,0:06:33.88,Default,,0,0,0,,But they’re going to have to deal \Nwith the Creator and his judgment.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.88,0:06:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And there are three Psalms \NI’d like to just mention briefly \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.28,0:06:39.72,Default,,0,0,0,,that I find very interesting \Nthat tie in nicely \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.72,0:06:43.05,Default,,0,0,0,,with the wickedness of the world \Nand what Jehovah will do. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.05,0:06:45.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Psalm 10:4: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.82,0:06:50.33,Default,,0,0,0,,“In his haughtiness,\Nthe wicked man makes no investigation;\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.33,0:06:52.73,Default,,0,0,0,,“all his thoughts are:\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.73,0:06:55.16,Default,,0,0,0,,‘There is no God.’” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.16,0:06:57.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Psalm 12:8: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.20,0:07:00.03,Default,,0,0,0,,“The wicked walk around unrestrained \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.03,0:07:03.71,Default,,0,0,0,,because the sons of men \Npromote depravity.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.71,0:07:06.08,Default,,0,0,0,,That could’ve been \Nthis morning’s headlines \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.08,0:07:08.21,Default,,0,0,0,,in The New York Times. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.21,0:07:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And the last, \NPsalm 92:7: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.11,0:07:13.98,Default,,0,0,0,,“When the wicked sprout like weeds \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.98,0:07:16.49,Default,,0,0,0,,“and all the wrongdoers flourish, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.49,0:07:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,it is that they \Nmay be annihilated forever.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.16,0:07:22.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And to that we say: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.46,0:07:22.98,Default,,0,0,0,,“Amen.\NSo be it!”\N
